      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is my FreeBSD soundtrack collection: small tracks inspired by FreeBSD releases, experiments, desktop and server experience that becomes part of everyday life.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;freebsd-151-release&#34;&gt;FreeBSD 15.1-RELEASE&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Jun 16 2026.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;mt-6 audio-player text-black rounded-xl p-6 min-h-[220px] relative overflow-hidden flex items-center&#34;&#xA;  data-audio-src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/audio/FreeBSD_15.1-RELEASE.mp3&#34; style=&#34;background-image: url(&#39;/audio/freebsd-15.1-release-cover.png&#39;); background-size: cover; background-position: center;&#34; &gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;absolute inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-30 pointer-events-none&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div&#xA;    class=&#34;absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 top-0 bg-black bg-opacity-5 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/0 to-black/80 pointer-events-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;audio class=&#34;audio-element hidden&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;source src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/audio/FreeBSD_15.1-RELEASE.mp3&#34; type=&#34;audio/mpeg&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Your browser does not support the audio element.&#xA;  &lt;/audio&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;audio-content relative z-10 flex w-full min-w-0 items-center gap-8&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div&#xA;      class=&#34;cover-art-wrap relative shrink-0 cursor-pointer overflow-hidden rounded-xl shadow-lg transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out hover:scale-[1.02]&#34;&#xA;      role=&#34;button&#34; tabindex=&#34;0&#34; aria-label=&#34;Play or pause audio&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;      &lt;img class=&#34;cover-art block h-full w-full object-cover !mt-0&#34; src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/audio/freebsd-15.1-release-cover.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center bg-black bg-opacity-10&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;play-button-container relative h-16 w-16 shrink-0 rounded-full backdrop-blur-md&#34;&gt;&#xA;          &#xA;          &lt;div&#xA;            class=&#34;play-button-bg is-image-bg pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-0 rounded-full bg-black bg-opacity-25 transition-transform transition-colors duration-300 ease-in-out&#34;&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;          &#xA;          &lt;svg class=&#34;circular-progress pointer-events-none absolute left-0 top-0 z-20 h-16 w-16 -rotate-90&#34;&#xA;            viewBox=&#34;0 0 100 100&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;circle class=&#34;progress-bg&#34; cx=&#34;50&#34; cy=&#34;50&#34; r=&#34;46&#34;&#xA;              stroke=&#34;rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.28)&#34; stroke-width=&#34;4&#34;&#xA;              fill=&#34;none&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;circle class=&#34;progress-indicator&#34; cx=&#34;50&#34; cy=&#34;50&#34; r=&#34;46&#34;&#xA;              stroke=&#34;white&#34; stroke-width=&#34;4&#34; stroke-dasharray=&#34;289.027&#34;&#xA;              stroke-dashoffset=&#34;289.027&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; /&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;          &#xA;          &lt;div&#xA;            class=&#34;play-button relative z-30 flex h-16 w-16 cursor-pointer items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-transparent transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out hover:scale-110 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;flex transition-transform duration-100 ease-in-out group-hover:scale-110&#34;&gt;&#xA;              &lt;svg class=&#34;play-icon ml-1&#34; width=&#34;28&#34; height=&#34;29&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 23 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;                xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path&#xA;                  d=&#34;M4.86328 17.0763V5.73008C4.86328 4.67612 5.98644 4.00223 6.9164 4.49821L17.5535 10.1713C18.539 10.6969 18.539 12.1095 17.5535 12.6351L6.9164 18.3082C5.98643 18.8042 4.86328 18.1303 4.86328 17.0763Z&#34;&#xA;                  fill=&#34;white&#34; /&gt;&#xA;              &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;              &lt;svg class=&#34;pause-icon hidden&#34; width=&#34;18&#34; height=&#34;29&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 25&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;                xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path&#xA;                  d=&#34;M4.78357 0.535156C5.95923 0.535156 6.54733 0.534895 6.99646 0.763672C7.39159 0.965003 7.7131 1.28651 7.91443 1.68164C8.14331 2.13085 8.14294 2.71942 8.14294 3.89551V21.1748C8.14294 22.3509 8.14331 22.9395 7.91443 23.3887C7.71311 23.7837 7.39146 24.1044 6.99646 24.3057C6.54731 24.5345 5.95936 24.5352 4.78357 24.5352H3.70349C2.5274 24.5352 1.93883 24.5345 1.48962 24.3057C1.09466 24.1044 0.772953 23.7836 0.571655 23.3887C0.342772 22.9395 0.34314 22.3509 0.34314 21.1748V3.89551C0.34314 2.71947 0.342806 2.13084 0.571655 1.68164C0.772987 1.28651 1.09449 0.965003 1.48962 0.763672C1.93883 0.534803 2.52742 0.535156 3.70349 0.535156H4.78357ZM19.7015 0.535156C20.8772 0.535156 21.4653 0.534925 21.9144 0.763672C22.3096 0.964998 22.6311 1.28652 22.8324 1.68164C23.0613 2.13085 23.0609 2.71941 23.0609 3.89551V21.1748C23.0609 22.3509 23.0613 22.9395 22.8324 23.3887C22.6311 23.7837 22.3094 24.1044 21.9144 24.3057C21.4653 24.5345 20.8774 24.5352 19.7015 24.5352H18.6215C17.4454 24.5352 16.8568 24.5345 16.4076 24.3057C16.0126 24.1043 15.6909 23.7836 15.4896 23.3887C15.2607 22.9395 15.2611 22.3509 15.2611 21.1748V3.89551C15.2611 2.7195 15.2608 2.13084 15.4896 1.68164C15.6909 1.28652 16.0125 0.965005 16.4076 0.763672C16.8568 0.534789 17.4454 0.535156 18.6215 0.535156H19.7015Z&#34;&#xA;                  fill=&#34;white&#34; /&gt;&#xA;              &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div&#xA;      class=&#34;audio-info flex min-w-0 flex-1 flex-col justify-center text-left leading-[1.2] text-white&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;a class=&#34;block truncate text-xl font-semibold hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/audio/FreeBSD_15.1-RELEASE.mp3&#34; download&gt;&#xA;        FreeBSD_15.1-RELEASE.mp3&#xA;      &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;mt-1 text-xs font-medium opacity-80&#34;&gt;&#xA;        Click to download&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;      &lt;input class=&#34;seekbar audio-seekbar&#34; type=&#34;range&#34; min=&#34;0&#34; max=&#34;100&#34; value=&#34;0&#34; step=&#34;0.1&#34; aria-label=&#34;Seek audio&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;audio-time-indicator mt-1 text-right text-xs font-medium tabular-nums opacity-80&#34; aria-live=&#34;off&#34;&gt;&#xA;        0:00 / 0:00&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div&#xA;    class=&#34;ai-music-tag absolute bottom-3 right-3 z-20 text-xs font-medium opacity-15 text-white&#34;&gt;&#xA;    AI music&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;  .audio-player {&#xA;    box-sizing: border-box;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-content {&#xA;    min-height: 150px;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .cover-art-wrap {&#xA;    width: 150px;&#xA;    height: 150px;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .cover-art-wrap::after {&#xA;    content: &#34;&#34;;&#xA;    position: absolute;&#xA;    inset: 0;&#xA;    z-index: 40;&#xA;    border-radius: inherit;&#xA;    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);&#xA;    pointer-events: none;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-info {&#xA;    max-width: 100%;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .play-button-bg {&#xA;    transform: scale(1);&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .play-button-container:hover .play-button-bg {&#xA;    transform: scale(1.1);&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .play-button-container:hover .play-button-bg.is-image-bg {&#xA;    --tw-bg-opacity: 0.4;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar {&#xA;    --progress: 0%;&#xA;    --track-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22);&#xA;    --track-fill: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);&#xA;&#xA;    -webkit-appearance: none;&#xA;    appearance: none;&#xA;    display: block;&#xA;    width: 100%;&#xA;    height: 14px;&#xA;    margin: 22px 0 0 0;&#xA;    cursor: pointer;&#xA;    background: transparent;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-time-indicator {&#xA;    line-height: 1;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar::-webkit-slider-runnable-track {&#xA;    height: 5px;&#xA;    border-radius: 999px;&#xA;    background:&#xA;      linear-gradient(to right,&#xA;        var(--track-fill) 0%,&#xA;        var(--track-fill) var(--progress),&#xA;        var(--track-bg) var(--progress),&#xA;        var(--track-bg) 100%);&#xA;    box-shadow: inset 0 1px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16);&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar::-moz-range-track {&#xA;    height: 5px;&#xA;    border-radius: 999px;&#xA;    background: var(--track-bg);&#xA;    box-shadow: inset 0 1px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16);&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar::-moz-range-progress {&#xA;    height: 5px;&#xA;    border-radius: 999px;&#xA;    background: var(--track-fill);&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar::-webkit-slider-thumb {&#xA;    -webkit-appearance: none;&#xA;    appearance: none;&#xA;    width: 0;&#xA;    height: 0;&#xA;    border: 0;&#xA;    box-shadow: none;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar::-moz-range-thumb {&#xA;    width: 0;&#xA;    height: 0;&#xA;    border: 0;&#xA;    box-shadow: none;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  .audio-seekbar:focus-visible,&#xA;  .cover-art-wrap:focus-visible,&#xA;  .play-button:focus-visible {&#xA;    outline: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);&#xA;    outline-offset: 3px;&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  @media (max-width: 768px) {&#xA;    .audio-player {&#xA;      min-height: auto;&#xA;      padding: 1.25rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .audio-content {&#xA;      gap: 1rem;&#xA;      min-height: 120px;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .cover-art-wrap {&#xA;      width: 120px;&#xA;      height: 120px;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .play-button-container,&#xA;    .circular-progress,&#xA;    .play-button {&#xA;      width: 3.5rem;&#xA;      height: 3.5rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .audio-seekbar {&#xA;      margin-top: 18px;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .ai-music-tag {&#xA;      bottom: 0.75rem;&#xA;      right: 0.75rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;  }&#xA;&#xA;  @media (max-width: 520px) {&#xA;    .audio-player {&#xA;      padding: 1rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .audio-content {&#xA;      flex-direction: column;&#xA;      align-items: stretch;&#xA;      gap: 1rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .cover-art-wrap {&#xA;      width: 100%;&#xA;      height: auto;&#xA;      aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;&#xA;      max-width: 180px;&#xA;      align-self: center;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .audio-info {&#xA;      width: 100%;&#xA;      text-align: center;&#xA;      padding-bottom: 1.5rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .audio-seekbar {&#xA;      margin-top: 18px;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    .ai-music-tag {&#xA;      bottom: 0.75rem;&#xA;      right: 1rem;&#xA;    }&#xA;  }&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;script&gt;&#xA;  (function () {&#xA;    &#xA;    const players = document.querySelectorAll(&#39;.audio-player&#39;);&#xA;    const player = players[players.length - 1];&#xA;&#xA;    if (!player) {&#xA;      return;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    const audio = player.querySelector(&#39;.audio-element&#39;);&#xA;    const playBtn = player.querySelector(&#39;.play-button&#39;);&#xA;    const coverArtWrap = player.querySelector(&#39;.cover-art-wrap&#39;);&#xA;    const playIcon = player.querySelector(&#39;.play-icon&#39;);&#xA;    const pauseIcon = player.querySelector(&#39;.pause-icon&#39;);&#xA;    const progressIndicator = player.querySelector(&#39;.progress-indicator&#39;);&#xA;    const seekbar = player.querySelector(&#39;.seekbar&#39;);&#xA;    const timeIndicator = player.querySelector(&#39;.audio-time-indicator&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;    if (!audio || !playBtn || !playIcon || !pauseIcon || !progressIndicator) {&#xA;      return;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    let isSeeking = false;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    const radius = parseFloat(progressIndicator.getAttribute(&#39;r&#39;));&#xA;    const circumference = 2 * Math.PI * radius;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    progressIndicator.style.strokeDasharray = circumference;&#xA;    progressIndicator.style.strokeDashoffset = circumference;&#xA;&#xA;    function toggleIcons(isPlaying) {&#xA;      if (isPlaying) {&#xA;        playIcon.classList.add(&#39;hidden&#39;);&#xA;        pauseIcon.classList.remove(&#39;hidden&#39;);&#xA;      } else {&#xA;        pauseIcon.classList.add(&#39;hidden&#39;);&#xA;        playIcon.classList.remove(&#39;hidden&#39;);&#xA;      }&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function updateProgress(percent) {&#xA;      const offset = circumference - (percent / 100) * circumference;&#xA;      progressIndicator.style.strokeDashoffset = offset;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function updateSeekbarFill() {&#xA;      if (!seekbar || !audio.duration) {&#xA;        return;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      const percent = (audio.currentTime / audio.duration) * 100;&#xA;      seekbar.style.setProperty(&#39;--progress&#39;, `${percent}%`);&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function formatTime(seconds) {&#xA;      if (!Number.isFinite(seconds) || seconds &lt; 0) {&#xA;        return &#39;0:00&#39;;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      const totalSeconds = Math.floor(seconds);&#xA;      const minutes = Math.floor(totalSeconds / 60);&#xA;      const remainingSeconds = totalSeconds % 60;&#xA;&#xA;      return `${minutes}:${String(remainingSeconds).padStart(2, &#39;0&#39;)}`;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function updateTimeIndicator() {&#xA;      if (!timeIndicator) {&#xA;        return;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      const currentTime = Number.isFinite(audio.currentTime) ? audio.currentTime : 0;&#xA;      const duration = Number.isFinite(audio.duration) ? audio.duration : 0;&#xA;&#xA;      timeIndicator.textContent = `${formatTime(currentTime)} / ${formatTime(duration)}`;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function updateSeekbar() {&#xA;      if (!seekbar || isSeeking || !audio.duration) {&#xA;        return;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      seekbar.value = audio.currentTime;&#xA;      updateSeekbarFill();&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function seekTo(value) {&#xA;      if (!audio.duration) {&#xA;        return;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      audio.currentTime = Math.min(Math.max(parseFloat(value) || 0, 0), audio.duration);&#xA;&#xA;      const percent = (audio.currentTime / audio.duration) * 100;&#xA;      updateProgress(percent);&#xA;      updateSeekbarFill();&#xA;      updateTimeIndicator();&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function getTrackName() {&#xA;      const src = audio.currentSrc || audio.querySelector(&#39;source&#39;)?.src || player.dataset.audioSrc || &#39;&#39;;&#xA;&#xA;      try {&#xA;        const url = new URL(src, window.location.href);&#xA;        return decodeURIComponent(url.pathname.split(&#39;/&#39;).filter(Boolean).pop() || &#39;unknown-track&#39;);&#xA;      } catch (error) {&#xA;        return decodeURIComponent(src.split(&#39;/&#39;).filter(Boolean).pop() || &#39;unknown-track&#39;);&#xA;      }&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function slugify(value) {&#xA;      return value&#xA;        .replace(/\.[^/.]+$/, &#39;&#39;)&#xA;        .toLowerCase()&#xA;        .trim()&#xA;        .replace(/&amp;/g, &#39;and&#39;)&#xA;        .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, &#39;-&#39;)&#xA;        .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, &#39;&#39;) || &#39;unknown-track&#39;;&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function trackPlaybackTap() {&#xA;      if (!window.goatcounter) {&#xA;        return;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      const trackName = getTrackName();&#xA;      const trackSlug = slugify(trackName);&#xA;      const eventName = `music-${trackSlug}-play`;&#xA;&#xA;      window.goatcounter.count({&#xA;        path: eventName,&#xA;        title: eventName,&#xA;        event: true,&#xA;      });&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function resetOtherPlayers() {&#xA;      document.querySelectorAll(&#39;.audio-element&#39;).forEach(otherAudio =&gt; {&#xA;        if (otherAudio === audio || otherAudio.paused) {&#xA;          return;&#xA;        }&#xA;&#xA;        otherAudio.pause();&#xA;&#xA;        const otherPlayer = otherAudio.closest(&#39;.audio-player&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;        if (!otherPlayer) {&#xA;          return;&#xA;        }&#xA;&#xA;        const otherPlayIcon = otherPlayer.querySelector(&#39;.play-icon&#39;);&#xA;        const otherPauseIcon = otherPlayer.querySelector(&#39;.pause-icon&#39;);&#xA;        const otherProgressIndicator = otherPlayer.querySelector(&#39;.progress-indicator&#39;);&#xA;        const otherSeekbar = otherPlayer.querySelector(&#39;.seekbar&#39;);&#xA;        const otherTimeIndicator = otherPlayer.querySelector(&#39;.audio-time-indicator&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;        if (otherPauseIcon &amp;&amp; otherPlayIcon) {&#xA;          otherPauseIcon.classList.add(&#39;hidden&#39;);&#xA;          otherPlayIcon.classList.remove(&#39;hidden&#39;);&#xA;        }&#xA;&#xA;        if (otherProgressIndicator) {&#xA;          const otherRadius = parseFloat(otherProgressIndicator.getAttribute(&#39;r&#39;));&#xA;          const otherCircumference = 2 * Math.PI * otherRadius;&#xA;          otherProgressIndicator.style.strokeDashoffset = otherCircumference;&#xA;        }&#xA;&#xA;        if (otherSeekbar) {&#xA;          otherSeekbar.value = 0;&#xA;          otherSeekbar.style.setProperty(&#39;--progress&#39;, &#39;0%&#39;);&#xA;        }&#xA;&#xA;        if (otherTimeIndicator) {&#xA;          const otherDuration = Number.isFinite(otherAudio.duration) ? otherAudio.duration : 0;&#xA;          otherTimeIndicator.textContent = `0:00 / ${formatTime(otherDuration)}`;&#xA;        }&#xA;      });&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    function togglePlayback() {&#xA;      if (audio.paused) {&#xA;        resetOtherPlayers();&#xA;&#xA;        audio.play()&#xA;          .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;            trackPlaybackTap();&#xA;          })&#xA;          .catch(error =&gt; {&#xA;            console.error(&#39;Audio playback failed:&#39;, error);&#xA;          });&#xA;      } else {&#xA;        audio.pause();&#xA;      }&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    playBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, event =&gt; {&#xA;      event.stopPropagation();&#xA;      togglePlayback();&#xA;    });&#xA;&#xA;    if (coverArtWrap) {&#xA;      coverArtWrap.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, togglePlayback);&#xA;&#xA;      coverArtWrap.addEventListener(&#39;keydown&#39;, event =&gt; {&#xA;        if (event.key === &#39;Enter&#39; || event.key === &#39; &#39;) {&#xA;          event.preventDefault();&#xA;          togglePlayback();&#xA;        }&#xA;      });&#xA;    }&#xA;&#xA;    audio.addEventListener(&#39;play&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;      toggleIcons(true);&#xA;    });&#xA;&#xA;    audio.addEventListener(&#39;pause&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;      toggleIcons(false);&#xA;    });&#xA;&#xA;    audio.addEventListener(&#39;ended&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;      toggleIcons(false);&#xA;      audio.currentTime = 0;&#xA;      updateProgress(0);&#xA;&#xA;      if (seekbar) {&#xA;        seekbar.value = 0;&#xA;        seekbar.style.setProperty(&#39;--progress&#39;, &#39;0%&#39;);&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      updateTimeIndicator();&#xA;    });&#xA;&#xA;    audio.addEventListener(&#39;loadedmetadata&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;      if (seekbar &amp;&amp; audio.duration) {&#xA;        seekbar.max = audio.duration;&#xA;        seekbar.value = audio.currentTime;&#xA;        updateSeekbarFill();&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      updateTimeIndicator();&#xA;    });&#xA;&#xA;    audio.addEventListener(&#39;timeupdate&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;      if (!audio.duration) {&#xA;        return;&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      const percent = (audio.currentTime / audio.duration) * 100;&#xA;      updateProgress(percent);&#xA;      updateSeekbar();&#xA;      updateTimeIndicator();&#xA;    });&#xA;&#xA;    updateTimeIndicator();&#xA;&#xA;    if (seekbar) {&#xA;      seekbar.addEventListener(&#39;pointerdown&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;        isSeeking = true;&#xA;      });&#xA;&#xA;      seekbar.addEventListener(&#39;input&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;        seekTo(seekbar.value);&#xA;      });&#xA;&#xA;      seekbar.addEventListener(&#39;change&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;        seekTo(seekbar.value);&#xA;        isSeeking = false;&#xA;      });&#xA;&#xA;      seekbar.addEventListener(&#39;pointerup&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;        seekTo(seekbar.value);&#xA;        isSeeking = false;&#xA;      });&#xA;&#xA;      seekbar.addEventListener(&#39;pointercancel&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;        isSeeking = false;&#xA;        updateSeekbar();&#xA;      });&#xA;    }&#xA;  })();&#xA;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;details&gt;&#xA;&lt;summary&gt;FreeBSD 15.1-RELEASE Lyrics &lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;verse-1&#34;&gt;Verse 1&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;June heat on the console, &lt;br/&gt;&#xA;fifteen-one comes alive,&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;second spark of stable branches,&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;kernels burning, systems thrive.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Fit the FreeBSD Logo in a Perfect Circle</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 12:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The FreeBSD and Apple logos are quite similar. &lt;br/&gt;&#xA;Both have a heavy base and leaves / tails on top.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/apple-freebsd-wrong-circle-fit.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Apple and FreeBSD logos compared by their heavy base and top detail, followed by a wrong circular crop approach&#34; width=&#34;928&#34; height=&#34;200&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;this-is-how-apple-fits-its-logo-into-a-circle&#34;&gt;This is how Apple fits its logo into a circle&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/apple-homepod-logo.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Apple logo centered on the circular top surface of a black HomePod&#34; width=&#34;1472&#34; height=&#34;980&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;With guides:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/apple-homepod-circle-guides.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Apple HomePod top with orange circular guides around the speaker surface and Apple logo&#34; width=&#34;1472&#34; height=&#34;980&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>I Connected a Desktop Phone to a FreeBSD Server, so Now I Can Call It</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/desktop-phone-connected-to-freebsd-server/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 09:00:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/desktop-phone-connected-to-freebsd-server/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I turned a Panasonic KX-T2315 desk phone into a physical menu for my FreeBSD server. When I pick up the handset, the phone adapter calls Asterisk, waits for one digit, and triggers a predefined script on the FreeBSD server. This post covers the phone restoration, HT801 setup, Asterisk configuration, Lua dialplan, Python AGI dispatcher, and the full config download.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The basic flow looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#abb2bf;background-color:#282c34;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Panasonic KX-T2315 analog phone&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;|&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;| FXS phone cable&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;v&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Grandstream HT801&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;|&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;| SIP + RTP&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;v&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;FreeBSD &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d19a66&#34;&gt;14&lt;/span&gt; + Asterisk&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;|&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;| AGI&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;v&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Python dispatcher&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;|&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;v&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Predefined server-side scripts&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/desktop-phone-connected-to-freebsd-server/images/Panasonic-KX-T2315-connected-to-FreeBSD-schema_hu_3aec6ad49b3e04ae.webp&#34; srcset=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/desktop-phone-connected-to-freebsd-server/images/Panasonic-KX-T2315-connected-to-FreeBSD-schema_hu_d49850d9118382c8.webp 480w, https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/desktop-phone-connected-to-freebsd-server/images/Panasonic-KX-T2315-connected-to-FreeBSD-schema_hu_b6509bb42eab9508.webp 768w, https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/desktop-phone-connected-to-freebsd-server/images/Panasonic-KX-T2315-connected-to-FreeBSD-schema_hu_3aec6ad49b3e04ae.webp 1200w&#34; sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 768px, calc(100vw - 2rem)&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; width=&#34;1200&#34; height=&#34;600&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Match FreeBSD’s YouTube Seeking Speed on macOS</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/how-i-match-freebsd-youtube-speed-on-macos/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Nov 2025 12:55:15 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/how-i-match-freebsd-youtube-speed-on-macos/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;On FreeBSD, YouTube seeking feels instant: click anywhere on the seek bar and playback resumes immediately. On macOS, Firefox gave me a short pause after each seek.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The fix that worked for me was &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; global macOS TCP tuning. Those system-wide tweaks can affect other apps. The stable solution was Firefox-only: keep HTTP/3/QUIC enabled, give Firefox a much larger media cache, reduce media throttling, and prefer the faster MP4/H.264 path over AV1/WebM MSE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>MATE on FreeBSD: macOS-Like Setup Guide: Font Rendering, UI Tweaks, and Settings</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/mate-on-freebsd-macos-like-setup-guide-font-rendering-ui-tweaks-and-settings/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 23 May 2025 20:38:13 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/mate-on-freebsd-macos-like-setup-guide-font-rendering-ui-tweaks-and-settings/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fonts&#34;&gt;Font rendering settings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#keyboard_and_mouse&#34;&gt;Keyboard and mouse settings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#interface&#34;&gt;Interface settings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#tearing&#34;&gt;Turn on TearFree&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#wallpapers&#34;&gt;Wallpapers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#mate_theme&#34;&gt;macOS theme for Mate&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#mate_spotlight&#34;&gt;Spotlight replacement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As I mentioned earlier, I noticed similarities between FreeBSD and macOS—after 20 years of using macOS, returning to FreeBSD feels like coming home. But I don’t like the font rendering used in non-macOS systems. Partly because Apple did it very well — &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.typeroom.eu/steve-jobs-calligraphy-apple-typography-legacy&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;nofollow&#34;&gt;Steve Jobs had a great understanding of typography&lt;/a&gt; — and partly because I’m just used to it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Install the FreeBSD AMDGPU Driver on a Beelink SER5 5560U</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/how-to-install-freebsd-amdgpu-driver-beelink-ser5-5560u/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 22 May 2025 22:45:11 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/how-to-install-freebsd-amdgpu-driver-beelink-ser5-5560u/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After installing FreeBSD 14.2 fresh on my Beelink SER5 5560U, I installed the GPU driver and enabled the TearFree option for better desktop usage by following these steps:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/how-to-install-freebsd-amdgpu-driver-beelink-ser5-5560u/Beelink-SER5-5560U.webp&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; width=&#34;2000&#34; height=&#34;1174&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-speed-up-keyboard-repeat-rate&#34;&gt;1. Speed Up Keyboard Repeat Rate&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#abb2bf;background-color:#282c34;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7f848e&#34;&gt;# kbdcontrol -r fast&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Edit &lt;code&gt;/etc/rc.conf&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#abb2bf;background-color:#282c34;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e06c75&#34;&gt;keyrate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#56b6c2&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#98c379&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;fast&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-install-xorg&#34;&gt;2. Install Xorg&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#abb2bf;background-color:#282c34;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7f848e&#34;&gt;# pkg install -y xorg&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;3-add-user-to-necessary-groups&#34;&gt;3. Add User to Necessary Groups&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#abb2bf;background-color:#282c34;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7f848e&#34;&gt;# pw groupmod video -m username&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7f848e&#34;&gt;# pw groupmod wheel -m username&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Verify with:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Comparing Performance of MacBook Pro M1 Pro to Mini PC on FreeBSD</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/freebsd-vs-macos-for-daily-use-my-personal-migration-story/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 19 May 2025 22:15:36 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/freebsd-vs-macos-for-daily-use-my-personal-migration-story/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As a designer I&amp;rsquo;ve been using macOS since 2005, but with each new update, I dislike the direction Apple is heading in. They add unnecessary features that use system resources and can&amp;rsquo;t be disabled. My seven-year-old MacBook Pro with an Intel processor became so slow and unresponsive with the latest macOS version that I can&amp;rsquo;t use it at all anymore. If your Mac can&amp;rsquo;t handle the latest macOS version, the only solution is to buy a more powerful Mac. This is probably fine, people upgrade their hardware from time to time, and this is part of the evolution of the field. However, Apple can deem any five-year-old Mac obsolete. It seems like they have more control over your computer than you do.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Can Cheap MiniPC with FreeBSD 14 Outperform MacBook Pro M1 Pro?</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/can-cheap-minipc-with-freebsd-14-outperform-macbook-pro-m1-pro/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Feb 2025 22:25:51 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/can-cheap-minipc-with-freebsd-14-outperform-macbook-pro-m1-pro/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;tldr&#34;&gt;TL;DR&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I put my €1800 MacBook Pro M1 Pro head-to-head with a €300 mini PC and found the cheaper option surprisingly fast. While the mini PC couldn&amp;rsquo;t completely replace my Mac for work due to some software and hardware limitations, it made me question the need for expensive purchases. Do we really need the latest and greatest hardware to be productive? Or are we being pushed to constantly upgrade for features we might not even fully utilize?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
